# Formation of the [[Unsorted/Earth\|Earth]]


## Timescales:
- Universe is 13.8byo
- Earth is 4.6byo

![t0_1d_history_v7_480.png](data:image/png;base64,)


- Astronomers estimate the age of the ***universe*** by studying the CMB and the doppler effect
- Doppler effect
	- When moving away, redshifted
	- When moving towards, blueshifted


## The Nebular Theory
- Current best explanation for the formation of the ***solar system***
- The process
	- Start with nebula of gas, dust, and metal
		- Hydrogen, helium
		- Silicates
		- Metals
	- Condenses into flattened disk shape
	- Young star forms
		- Nuclear fusion begins
			- Hydrogen-1 > Deuterium > Helium-3 / Tritium > Helium-4
		- Protoplanetary disk forms around it
		- The star rotates much faster because its matter is condensed into the  
	- Solar wind blows material away from the sun
	- Planets form through accretion
- Evidence
	- Planet arrangement
		- Rocky inner plants, gaseous outer planets
		- Solar wind strips light gasses from the inner planets, causing it to accumulate into the outer gas giants
		- All planets orbit in the same direction 

## Differentiation and evolution of the [[Unsorted/Earth\|Earth]]
- History
	- We discovered that the Earth has layers from analysis of seismic activity
		- By realizing that earthquakes on one side of the planet do not propagate to the other side
	- ![A_006_shadowzone4_swave_thumbnail.jpg](data:image/png;base64,)
- Layers
	- Inner core
		- 5150-6370km, 20%
		- Iron, heavy elements
	- Outer core
		- 2890-5150km 35%
	- Mantle
		- 40-2890km, 45%
		- Mineral elements
			- Aluminum, Magnesium, Silicon
	- Crust
		- 0-40km, 0.6%

## The Hadean Era
- The Great Bombardment
	- Even greater while it was first forming, settled over time
- Heat of formation
	- Due to all of the meteor impacts
	- Why the Earth has a molten core to this day
	- Causes
		- Radioactive Decay
		- Heat of Sun
		- Friction due to high pressure
		- Tidal forces from the moon
	- Mars has cooled down
		- Perhaps because it's smaller?
- The Great Bombardment
- [[Unsorted/Plate Tectonics\|Plate Tectonics]]
	- Have slowed down since about 2bya
	- Pangea - 252mya
